Mingi välibaar, kust kostub väga vali muusika. Review: 
There is a clear emphasis on a party atmosphere promoted by the hotel that is not clear. The pictures omit the permanent fixtures of speakers at the lobby and main pool aswell as in floor speakers throughout the hotel. This combined with the open air nightclub outside the hotel that is not clearly advertised means that our stay was far from the relaxing holiday we were hoping for. At points around Insula pool I could hear 3 different song playing from speakers at the bar, in the grass and from the other pool which is not appropriate. The volume of both the music during the day and the evening entertainment means that there is virtually nowhere you can go in the facility where music cannot be heard, even on the balcony the music from the ground speakers can be heard! This may be the atmosphere that others enjoy and the White Hills are promoting but this needs to be clearly advertised as there is no avoiding the noise and excessively loud music/entertainment. We moved rooms after being kept awake until 3:30am by the Saturday night “Vibe club” on our second night and still from almost the furthest point back in the hotel all the music at the front of the hotel and from the lobby could be heard.

 Also, if you have young kids, please note they will have loud party until 11pm.
